        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer41311670" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16100594315987381320">The first book known to have been written by a woman in the English language. Julian is loved by feminist theologians and Catholic conservatives alike. Out of her mystical visions of Christ, comes an exploration of the feminine aspects of God, the problem of evil and suffering, and God&apos;s love for humanity. Most known for the phrase &quot;all shall be well&quot;, but I also love &quot;Love was His meaning&quot;. I love this book. </span>
  <span id="freeText16100594315987381320" style="display:none">The first book known to have been written by a woman in the English language. Julian is loved by feminist theologians and Catholic conservatives alike. Out of her mystical visions of Christ, comes an exploration of the feminine aspects of God, the problem of evil and suffering, and God's love for humanity. Most known for the phrase "all shall be well", but I also love "Love was His meaning". I love this book. </span>
